> [{quoted}](name=Kelg,realm=NA,application-id=LqLKtMpN,discussion-id=5R6g525u,comment-id=0000,timestamp=2018-07-04T11:36:13.705+0000)
>
> Yeah it&#x27;s annoying and very noticeable since it happens pretty much any time you use an ability. I&#x27;m not sure how riot let this through without fixing it.
> {{sticker:zombie-brand-facepalm}}

They let it through because this patch was literally made for Darius, after he got buffed he got banned more often so this is mostly just a way to sell more Darius skins since people may be less likely to ban him if they can get mission progress. I mean think about it, the theme is supposed to be Darius vs Garen but everyone knows that Garen is just a much much much worse off version of Darius. They should've buffed Garen before they made this rediculous VS thing, every other VS event was much more even. Not to mention the issue where Garen mission progress wasn't being counted. I literally haven't even played since this patch because of all the issues I've been hearing about. Why Garen gets a "God-King" skin when the only time he can ever feel god-like is against bad players is beyond me. I'd probably have bought the skin too if Riot wasn't busy being the Blizzard of balance with flavor of the month design choices. {{sticker:zombie-brand-facepalm}}
